commText: We're back for the chase.. A new opening pair for Punjab KIngs, it's Prabhsimran Singh and Sam Curran. Gerald Coetzee with the new ball for MI - they've made their impact sub, Akash Madhwal replaces Suryakumar Yadav

Suryakumar Yadav: That teaches you there are ups and downs in life (on his scores this season). It is going really, I am almost there, I have started fielding and training, hoping I will be on the field for the whole 40 overs. Nothing much (on his celebration), there was a batters meeting and we spoke about a batter batting for 15-16 overs, took a little more time today but once Rohit got out, someone had to bat deep. There hasn't been dew and if that is the case then it is way above par.

21:24 Local Time, 15:54 GMT, 21:24 IST: Mumbai Indians have finished with a respectable score, but it's worth remembering that they've conceded 195 or more four times out of six games so far. Can they defend this total against a strong PBKS batting unit? They lost Ishan Kishan early, but Rohit and Suryakumar strung together a half-century partnership. The latter then joined forces with Tilak Varma to add 49 more runs for the third wicket - handy cameos from Tim David and Hardik Pandya boosted the score in the final few overs, but PBKS did keep themselves in the hunt with handy wickets. The pitch is slightly on the slower side and they'll hope for no dew in the second innings. Three wickets for Harshal and two for Curran. We'll be back shortly for the chase.

Harshal Patel to Nabi, out Nabi Run Out!! Nabi has been run-out at the bowler's end and MI finish with 192. Was very full and at the stumps, Nabi backed away and clattered it straight back at the stumps - they were always going for the single, but the ball rolled to the off-side, Harshal runs across, picks the ball, runs back and takes a stump out, catching the hapless batter short by a country mile. Nabi run out (Harshal Patel) 0(1)
Harshal Patel to Nabi, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!
Mohammad Nabi, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshal Patel to Shepherd, out Caught by Shashank Singh!! Harshal is chipping away at useful wickets in the 20th over - another slower ball into the pitch, angled into the right-hander and Shepherd was looking to use that angle to help it over long leg - but he's completely undone by the slowness of the delivery, he's through with the swing early and drags it off the inner half, straight down Shashank's throat at long leg. Shepherd c Shashank Singh b Harshal Patel 1(2)
Harshal Patel to Shepherd, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Harshal Patel to Tilak Varma, 1 run, another slower ball from Harshal, bowled into the pitch and gives Tilak no pace on the swing - dragged down towards long-on for a single
A dead ball as Tilak Varma swings one straight into the spider cam - was the slower ball and he shovelled the lofted drive, the ball dropping down in no man's land
Harshal Patel to Shepherd, 1 run, fuller length delivery on off, dragged down to long-on for a single
Romario Shepherd, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshal Patel to Tim David, out Caught by Sam Curran!! A second wicket for Harshal - was the slower ball, bowled into the pitch and doesn't give the pace for David to swing, he went hard and flat, but straight down Curran's throat at long-off. An useful knock from David ends. Tim David c Sam Curran b Harshal Patel 14(7) [4s-2 6s-1]
Harshal Patel to Tim David, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Tim David, leg byes, FOUR, appeal for LBW, it looks plumb, but the onfield call is NOT OUT, they've reviewed. No bat and UltraEdge confirms it. Onto ball-tracking: The impact is outside off and it's missing the off-stump, a good call from the umpire and they've lost a review. Slower ball on off, dips onto David and he's undone by the change of pace, was looking to slog it onto the on-side and missed, the ball runs away to the third man ropes for leg byes, four of them
Appeal for LBW, it looks plumb, but the onfield call is NOT OUT, they've reviewed
Hardik vs Harshal in IPL 5 inngs 13 balls 13 runs 3 dismissals
Harshal Patel to Tim David, wide, banged in short and well wide of off, David can't reach out, it's well past the tramlines and is called as a wide

Sam Curran to Tim David, byes, 1 run, short of a good length and angling down leg, David got a long way across on the swipe and missed - so did Jitesh Sharma as he palmed it away, they take an extra run and it's given as a wide, but PBKS have reviewed, replays show that the ball would've hit David on his body had he stayed the line, it's changed much to David's disappointment
Sam Curran to Tim David, SIX, massive, the slower ball from Curran, but David spotted it early, gets across and clubs it high and over mid-wicket, went sailing over the ropes for a maximum
Sam Curran to Tim David, FOUR, banged in short by Curran - David shuffles across, swivels and then pulls it past square leg, no one in the deep and it's another boundary
Sam Curran to Tim David, wide, the slower ball from Curran, but he's pushed it miles wide of off, called as a wide
Sam Curran to Tim David, FOUR, short, wide and four, width on offer from Curran - David gets on top of the bounce and then clatters it past cover-point, bounces away to the ropes

Sam Curran to Tim David, wide, the slower ball from Curran, pushed across the right-hander who looks to cut and missed, it's not given as a wide and MI review, but this is marginally outside the tramlines. David was slightly past the off-stump when he swung and missed, but it's still given as a wide
Sam Curran to Tim David, no run, on a length and angling across the right-hander, David went hard on the drive and finds the fielder at cover-point
Sam Curran to Tilak Varma, 1 run, another slower ball, full and at the stumps, Tilak swings and drags it off the inner half, past mid-wicket for a single
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshal Patel to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by Harpreet Brar!! A one-handed swipe and Hardik has holed out to deep mid-wicket. Was the slower short ball from Harshal, angled into the right-hander and cramped him for room - he swung lustily, doesn't get anywhere near the middle of the bat and it's another sitter for Brar, this time in front of the ropes at mid-wicket. Hardik Pandya c Harpreet Brar b Harshal Patel 10(6) [6s-1]
Harshal Patel to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Harshal Patel to Hardik Pandya, 2 runs, back of a length and well wide of off, Hardik stays leg-sided and then slaps the drive past cover, he's back for the second
Harshal Patel to Tilak Varma, 1 run, another slower ball from Harshal, the line is wide as well and Tilak can't get hold of the drive, scoops off the inner half towards long-off

Harshal Patel to Tilak Varma, SIX, smashed, a friendly short ball from Harshal - well outside off and it's hammered over mid-wicket, was attempting the slower ball, but it came at a friendly pace and at a nice height for Tilak
Harshal Patel to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, another full-toss from Harshal, once again the batter swings hard, this time it's Hardik and he mistimes it back past the bowler for a single
Harshal Patel to Tilak Varma, 1 run, a high full-toss from Harshal, but it's below the waist and he gets away - Tilak swung hard and gets an under-edge onto his body
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Hardik Pandya, SIX, thumped, tad too short from Curran - Pandya stays on the front-foot, picks the length early and then deposits the pull over mid-wicket, went soaring over the ropes

Sam Curran to Hardik Pandya, no run, on a good length and just outside off - Pandya is early into the pull and toe-ends it back at the bowler, Curran did get both hands on his follow-through, but he can't hold on
STAT: Suryakumar Yadav - 78 off 53 (SR 147.16). This is his 17th score of 75 or more in T20 cricket and the first time it came under a SR of 160.
Sam Curran to Tilak Varma, 1 run, low full-toss from Curran, driven through mid-wicket and the single brings up MI's 150
Sam Curran to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, punched to the left of mid-off where Liam Livingstone throws himself and makes the stop, saved three runs for his team
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Prabhsimran!! He's got his man now - perfect execution of the wide yorker from Curran - kept it full and away from Suryakumar's reach, the right-hander had to reach out on the drive, threw the kitchen sink and scooped the ball in the air - it's gone to the left of cover-point where Prabhsimran jumps and completes a fine two-handed catch. Was beginning to look very dangerous, but PBKS have nipped out Suryakumar at the right time. Suryakumar Yadav c Prabhsimran b Sam Curran 78(53) [4s-7 6s-3]
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, pace off from Curran, pushed across the right-hander, Suryakumar swipes across the line and misses
Sam Curran [2.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack
Can MI get 50 from the last 4 overs?

Rabada to Tilak Varma, SIX, crunched, back of a length and well wide of off - Tilak picks the length early, stays on the front-foot and then nails the pull over mid-wicket, sent it soaring into the stands for a maximum, 18 off the over
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, much better from Rabada - bowls the hard length on off, hit Suryakumar's bat and rolled towards cover for a single

Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, gorgeous, easy pickings for Suryakumar - full-toss on the pads, he gets inside the line, bringhs his wrists into play and then flicks it high and over long leg for a maximum
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, beautifully played. Suryakumar gets forward, makes room to a length ball and then goes inside out over cover, one bounce and over the ropes

Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, Suryakumar Yadav has been given OUT LBW, he's reviewed immediately. Is the ball sliding down leg? No bat and UltraEdge confirms it - onto ball-tracking: It's taking time to build and everyone waits anxiously, was the slower ball and the right-hander was early into the swing, but the angle is taking it down leg and it's another successful review, this time by Suryakumar Yadav. He was undone by the slowness of the ball and was through with the swipe early, struck in front of middle and leg
Surya reviewed immediately

Rabada to Tilak Varma, leg byes, 1 run, banged in short and angling across the left-hander, clonked Tilak's helmet as he's early into the pull, the ball rolls down to third man for a leg-bye. The physio is out for the mandatory concussion check, Tilak's fine and will continue
Kagiso Rabada [3.0-0-25-1] is back into the attack

Arshdeep Singh to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, that'll add salt to Arshdeep's wounds, on a good length and angling across the right-hander, Suryakumar throws his bat and then carves the drive over wide mid-off, 15 off the over

Arshdeep Singh to Suryakumar Yadav, wide, another wide yorker from Arshdeep - Suryakumar was staying leg-side and he can't reach out, not given as a wide and they've reviewed - it's clearly past the tramline and the original call has been changed, a marginal call going MI's way
Arshdeep Singh to Tilak Varma, 1 run, Arshdeep drags the length back on off, Tilak backs away and hacks the pull to long-on for a single

Arshdeep Singh to Tilak Varma, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Tilak - full and just outside off, he backsw away, opens up the gap wide of extra-cover and then drills the drive through that gap, much needed momentum for MI

Arshdeep Singh to Tilak Varma, FOUR, much needed boundary for MI - was the slower ball from Arshdeep, Tilak backed away, spotted the lack of pace, waited on the ball and then lofted it back over the bowler's head, mid-off was inside the ring, couple of bounces and over the ropes
Arshdeep Singh to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, the wide yorker now, Suryakumar reaches out and scoops a one-handed drive through cover-point for a saingle

Arshdeep Singh to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, slower ball pushed across the right-hander, Suryakumar went with hard hands on the drive and is undone by the lack of pace, bounces through to Jitesh Sharma
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
PBKS keeping things very tight, just 6 overs left and there's a lot of fuel left in MI's batting tank. Will both batters go after the bowling now?

Highlights (Overs 7-14) -- 61/1 -- Scoring rate slows down after powerplay -- Not the easiest pitches for batters to hit -- It's slow and low again -- Surya plays some lovely shots to inject momentum -- He gets to fifty off 34 balls -- Brar keeping things tight -- Curran removes Rohit for 36 (11.4)
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, full and following Suryakumar as he backed away, punched down to long-on for a single, 6 saingles off the over

Rabada to Tilak Varma, 1 run, banged in short and angled across the left-hander, Tilak swivels across and then flaps the pull over mid-wicket, bounces well in front of deep mid-wicket and it's just a single
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, Rabada keeps it full and on the leg-stump line as Suryakumar backed away, driven down to long-on for a single
Rabada to Tilak Varma, 1 run, banged in short and just outside off, pulled past square leg for a single
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, on a length and around off, punched off the back-foot to long-on for a single
Rabada to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, Tilak stays back and pushes it through mid-off for a single
Kagiso Rabada [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack

Timeout! Mumbai Indians have called for the break. They have the platform set and would like to discuss what would be a good score on this surface. There are still 7 overs left and they should be aiming for 180 minimum.
Harpreet Brar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, short and outside off, Tilak cuts square and the sweeper tidies up
Harpreet Brar to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, clipped between deep mid-wicket and long-on, Tilak collects a brace
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, slows it up outside off, Suryakumar eases it wide of extra cover
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, short of length and drifting in, whipped in front of square and Suryakumar picks up a couple
Harpreet Brar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, flatter and sliding across, Tilak punches to long-off
Stays round the wicket
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, tossed up around off, Suryakumar eases it to long-off
Harpreet Brar [2.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, I0$ good length ball on middle, Suryakumar punches to long-on
Sam Curran to Tilak Varma, 1 run, angled into the batter, Tilak tucks it backward of square leg
Tilak Varma, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Sam Curran to Rohit, out Caught by Harpreet Brar!! The skipper breaks the partnership. Rohit was not getting much strike in the last few overs, got struck on the helmet off the previous ball and departs now. He shimmies down the wicket to go big but Curran slowed the pace and angled it across, Rohit reaches for the drive and slices it to backward point, Brar with a good low catch. Rohit c Harpreet Brar b Sam Curran 36(25) [4s-2 6s-3]
Sam Curran to Rohit, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
The physio comes out now to check on Rohit and conduct a concussion test. He has a sip of water.
Sam Curran to Rohit, no run, I0$ slower ball and Rohit wanted to play the paddle backward of square, gets a top-edge and the ball ricochets onto the helmet. Curran checks with Rohit if he's fine
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, back of the hand slower ball, Suryakumar eases it to long-on
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, leg-lined delivery, Suryakumar flicks between deep mid-wicket and long-on, easy brace
Sam Curran [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Most sixes for MI in IPL 224* Rohit Sharma 223 K Pollard 104 H Pandya 103 I Kishan 97* Suryakumar Yadav
Harshal Patel to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, I0$ yorker around off, Suryakumar digs it to the off-side and retains strike
Harshal Patel to Rohit, 1 run, off-pace delivery and Rohit works it to long-on

Harshal Patel to Rohit, SIX, this is a mishit and the ball still sails over. Rohit enjoyed that, he has big smile on his face as he pumps gloves with SKY. Slower ball and Rohit was deceived, he was through the shot early and the ball goes straight up, Curran was settling near long-on but could only watch it sail over
Harshal Patel to Rohit, wide, short ball outside off, sprayed waywardly outside off and Rohit ignores
Harshal Patel to Rohit, no run, dipping slower ball, Rohit moves away and digs it back to Harshal

Harshal Patel to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, fifty for Suryakumar. He was on right from the time he walked out. 23rd IPL fifty and he raises his bat, shakes hand with Rohit and gives a thumbs up to someone. Slower short of length delivery, Suryakumar waits and pulls to deep mid-wicket
Harshal Patel to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, in-angler and Suryakumar turns it with soft hands in front of mid-wicket
Harshal Patel [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Livingstone to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, flatter delivery around off, Suryakumar knocks it to long-on
Livingstone to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, drags the length a tad, Suryakumar checks his push and picks out cover
Livingstone to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, fabulous shot! Suryakumar dances down, gives himself room and lofts it inside out towards deep extra cover, he got the height and managed to get it over the rope
Livingstone to Rohit, 1 run, drifts into leg-stump, Rohit nudges it to deep mid-wicket
Rohit was shaping to play the reverse sweep but Livingstone does not deliver. He aborts and the pair have a laugh
Livingstone to Rohit, no run, leg-break and turns away, Rohit guides it to backward point
Livingstone to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, tossed up around off, Suryakumar works it to long-on
Liam Livingstone [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack

Timeout! This is a solid start for Mumbai Indians. They lost Ishan in the third over but this pair have stitched a 50+ stand and as long as they bat there's every chance Mumbai will get close to 180-200. Punjab Kings haven't allowed them to run away with the run-rate but need wickets to keep it that way
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, shortens the length and slides in, Suryakumar flicks to long-on

Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, shot! He picked out deep backward square a couple of times in the previous over but not on this occasion, Suryakumar plays the sweep behind square and gets it nowhere close to a fielder

Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, drifting in with the angle, Suryakumar gets an under-edge on the sweep, the ball bounces into the ground and deflects off his back leg, Jitesh collects the ball and thinks it has come off the boot, but umpire Vineet Kulkarni got it spot on
Jitesh Sharma appeals for a catch. The umpire is not interested. He checks if Punjab are reviewing and they are not.
Harpreet Brar to Rohit, 1 run, drags the length a tad, Rohit knocks it wide of a diving Harpreet
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, flighted outside off, Suryakumar eases it to sweeper cover
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, tossed up on off, Suryakumar sweeps to short fine and there's a fumble, Rabada tidies up in the deep
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, low full toss on off, Suryakumar drives it to long-on

Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, that's a typical Suryakumar shot. He gets inside the line and whips it behind the wicket, shorter boundaries there but it wouldn't have mattered as he got it into the second tier
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, I0$ full pitcher around off, Suryakumar drives and finds mid-off
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, 148.2ks back of a length and nips in, Suryakumar ekes out an inside edge between his legs and the ball rolls away fine, just a brace
Rabada to Rohit, 1 run, I0$ very full delivery on off, Rohit drives it to long-on
Rabada to Rohit, no run, back of a length in-angler, Rohit misses the flick and is struck on the thigh pad
Kagiso Rabada [1.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Most sixes in Powerplay in IPL 2024 25 MI 21 SRH 20 KKR & DC
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, quicker and at the stumps, Suryakumar sweeps and picks out short fine
Harpreet Brar to Rohit, 1 run, I0$ delivery that drifts into the pads, Rohit nudges it backward of square
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, flatter and sliding in, Suryakumar works it wide of mid-wicket
Harpreet Brar to Rohit, 1 run, swept again and Rohit too picks out Rabada near deep backward square, just a single
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, I0$ quicker delivery on off, Suryakumar sweeps to deep backward square
Harpreet Brar to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, tossed up around off, Suryakumar eases it to cover
Harpreet Brar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Powerplay summary -- Arshdeep looks off-colour again -- Rabada strikes first ball, Kishan gone for 8 (2.1) -- Rohit given out LBW but decision is overturned (4.4) -- Pitch is typically low and slow

Sam Curran to Rohit, SIX, that's a fine way to end the powerplay. Slower ball and Rohit delayed his bat swing, he had made room to play the big shot but waited for it to land and then thumped it straight down the ground, just clearing the rope
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, leg-lined delivery and Suryakumar flicks to deep square leg

Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, Curran appeals for LBW. The umpire is not interested. Suryakumar looks to whip it into the leg-side, misses and is struck around the thigh. The ball had pitched outside leg and it was also going over
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, I0$ delivery with no room on offer, Suryakumar tucks it gently to mid-wicket
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, slower short ball and Suryakumar accepts it happily, he jumps off the ground and upper cuts it over short third. Safe shot to play with no one in the deep there
Sam Curran to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, I0$ back of a length delivery, Suryakumar turns it to mid-on
Sam Curran, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshal Patel to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, played with soft hands into the off-side and Suryakumar calls for an easy single
Harshal Patel to Rohit, 1 run, in-slanter on middle and leg, Rohit flicks it in front of square on the leg-side

Harshal Patel to Rohit, no run, that's an excellent review. In real time it looked out and hence umpire Vineet Kulkarni raised his finger. It was the dipping yorker and Rohit was completely deceived, the ball dips past his bat and strikes him on the boot. The impact was around middle and leg, ball-tracking showed it to be missing leg-stump

Mumbai review! Rohit is given out LBW. He has a chat with Suryakumar and decides to challenge the onfield. Was the ball going down leg? The impact is in front of middle and leg. Wickets is missing. Not Out
Harshal Patel to Rohit, no run, I0$ full pitcher outside off, Rohit wanted to smack it down the ground and was a tad early into the shot, toe-ends it to mid-off
Harshal Patel to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, once more slanting in and this time Suryakumar flicks it to deep square leg
Harshal Patel to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, in-angler on a fullish length, Suryakumar allows the ball to come and uses his wrists to whip it in front of square - between mid-wicket and mid-on
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Couple of ordinary overs from Arshdeep. The pace was down, hardly got past 135kph, and the length has been short and when he's gone full he has strayed onto the pads
Arshdeep Singh to Rohit, no run, I0$ back of a length around off, Rohit knocks it to point
Arshdeep Singh to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, I0$ full delivery down leg, Suryakumar toe-ends the whip backward of square leg
Arshdeep Singh to Rohit, 1 run, I0$ swinging into the batter, Rohit misses the clip and the ball deflects off the pad. But given as run
Arshdeep Singh to Rohit, SIX, this is bread and butter for Rohit. I0$ short of length delivery and it just sat up, Rohit dismisses the pull over deep mid-wicket and picks up a 80-meter six

Arshdeep Singh to Rohit, no run, decides to give the charge and Arshdeep saw that, banged it into the surface and got it to climb over Rohit's flashing blade, Jitesh gloves the ball and has a shy at the stumps, Rohit dives in to make his ground
Arshdeep Singh to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, I0$ back of a length delivery on off, Suryakumar knocks it to mid-off and crosses over
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, I0$ delivery on middle and leg, Suryakumar flicks it backward of square leg

Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, that's poor from Harshal. Short of length delivery and Suryakumar is cramped for room, he opens the bat face and steers it to the right of short third, Harshal moves across and does not bend down quickly to make the stop

Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, Suryakumar is off and running. I0$ delivery on middle-stump, Suryakumar uses his wrists and whips it over mid-wicket. Not quite off the middle but enough to get him going
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, on a length and around off, Suryakumar stabs it into the off-side
Rabada too has a wide slip
Rabada to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, I0$ good length ball outside off, Suryakumar mistimes the drive back to KG. He was looking to play that on the rise and the ball did not come on
Suryakumar Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Rabada to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Harpreet Brar!! Rabada cannot believe it. Ishan too walks off with a wry smile on his face. This was not a wicket-taking delivery but the Punjab management are not complaining, they have an early wicket. Short and outside off, Ishan does not bother to keep the cut down and slashes it straight to deep backward point, Brar takes a good catch over his head. Ishan Kishan c Harpreet Brar b Rabada 8(8) [4s-1]
Rabada to Ishan Kishan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Kagiso Rabada, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Arshdeep Singh to Rohit, no run, that's better. I0$ good length ball and it shapes away late, Rohit prods forward to defend but is beaten neck and crop. That should have been the line and length right through
Arshdeep Singh to Rohit, FOUR, I0$ very full delivery and it swings in nicely for Rohit to play the clip, he hits it uppishly but right between mid-wicket and mid-on
Arshdeep Singh to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, I0$ short and outside off, Ishan cuts square and the fielder from deep point tidies up

Arshdeep Singh to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, swing on offer but the length is short, Ishan throws his bat on the slash and gets a thick outside edge, the ball flies over short third and just bounces once before crossing the rope
Arshdeep Singh to Rohit, 1 run, I0$ swinging into leg-stump, Rohit helps it along the way to fine leg
One slip in place
Arshdeep Singh to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, short and outside off, Ishan cuts square and Brar with a good stop - dives to his right and takes the pace off
Arshdeep Singh, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
STAT: 250th IPL appearance for Rohit Sharma in IPL; second player to the milestone after MS Dhoni

Livingstone to Rohit, FOUR, ends the over with a boundary. Throws it up wide of off-stump, Rohit leans forward and caresses the drive past extra cover. The ball teases Curran only to beat him to the rope
Livingstone to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, short and Ishan was shaping to pull, but not much bounce and he adjusts to pull it to deep mid-wicket
Livingstone to Ishan Kishan, no run, flatter and quicker at I0$, Ishan punches it to cover
Livingstone to Rohit, 1 run, sticks with the off-break and strays onto the pads, Rohit nudges it backward of square
